==English==
===Etymology===
named for [[w:Max Planck|Max Planck]]
===Noun phrase===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Planck]]'s [[constant]]'''
#{{physics}} the [[constant]] of [[proportionality]] relating the [[energy]] and [[frequency]] of a [[photon]] (6.626 x 10<sup>-34</sup> [[joule]]-[[second]]s); also related to the [[indeterminacy]] [[limit]] in the [[Heisenberg uncertainty principle]]

